<subSubSection id="FFB3BC1D024C337734C80590C7B2C4EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="137310420B00A4BABC4D65852D9527A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4C208DFDED973FA99922F61F8C95473" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="EDCBB79DA8A94247ADA4807BCFD8C6AC" authority="Konstantinov &amp; Linzmeier, 2020" authorityName="Konstantinov &amp; Linzmeier" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Erinaceialtica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="janestanleyae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janestanleyae">janestanleyae</taxonomicName>
, is a matronym in honor of Jane Stanley of Bethesda, Maryland. We greatly appreciate Jane and her 
<normalizedToken id="28AF3195D36D34B32BEEE9183F965CB3" originalValue="family’s">family's</normalizedToken>
friendship and generosity in providing access and encouragement at the Punta Cana Resort, including use of their beautiful home, Casa de los 
<normalizedToken id="56F1BBCD455DAE9EE06435618621D20E" originalValue="Sueños">Suenos</normalizedToken>
, near the Ecological Reserve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
